result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Hearing on July 21, 2022 at 01:15 pm.

02:02 PM Defendant Rebecca A Nunez Santos appeared by Zoom, in custody, from Milwaukee House of Corrections.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Abigail Kincheloe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  All parties have agreed that some may have the hearing conducted remotely. This hearing has met the statutory standards for video conferencing.  The Court notes Attorney Kyle Jesinski was previously on this case and then Attorney Luis Gutierrez made an appearance indicating Attorney Jesinski would no longer be representing the defendant and a new attorney would be appointed.  As this moment, a new attorney has not been appointed.  Attorney Jesinski should NOT have been removed from this case as the case remains open.  The defendant states she spoke to an individual today from the Pulic Defender's Office and they stated she does qualify for Public Defender Respresentation and an attorney would be appointed.  The defendant further states she will be hospitalized beginning tomorrow at Columbia St. Mary's through the end of the year as she will undergo surgery and chemo.  The Court will set this matter back for status of counsel.  Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.  Bail remains as fixed.  Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  The defendant to appear by Zoom from Milwaukee HOC or the hospital at the next hearing.  Hearing scheduled for July 21, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
